12.That's really BIG for a Docker Image!
13.Docker images are supposed to be small and light weight. Let us try to trim it down.

Build a new smaller docker image by modifying the same Dockerfile and name it webapp-color and tag it lite.

Hint: Find a smaller base image for python:3.14. Make sure the final image is less than 150MB.

In the webapp-color directory, run the ls -l command to list the Dockerfile and other files.
And modify Dockerfile to use python:3.14-alpine image and then build using docker buildx build -t webapp-color:lite .

